nats.client

Interface SubscriptionIterator

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Closeable, Iterator<Message>

    public interface SubscriptionIterator
extends Iterator<Message>, Closeable
    Provides an Iterator for fetching Nats subscription messages in a blocking manner.
    Author:
    Mike Heath

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void close()
      Closes this subscription iterator.
      boolean hasNext()

      Returns the next Message sent by the Nats server.
      Message next(long timeout, TimeUnit unit)

      void remove()
      Throws an UnsupportedOperationException since you obviously can't remove a message after it has been received.

    • Method Detail

      • hasNext

        boolean hasNext()
        Returns true if this iterator is open. We do not know if/when the Nats server will publish another message so we assume another message is pending so, this method always returns true unless this iterator has been closed.

        Closing the subscription associated with this iterator will close this iterator.

        Specified by:
        hasNext in interface Iterator<Message>
        Returns:
        true unless this iterator has been closed.

      • next

        Message next(long timeout,
           TimeUnit unit)
             throws NatsClosedException
        Returns the next Message sent by the Nats server within the specified time limit.
        Parameters:
        timeout - the maximum time to wait for a message
        unit - the time unit of the timeout argument
        Returns:
        the next Message sent by the Nats server or null if a message didn't arrive within the specified time limit.
        Throws:
        NatsClosedException - thrown if the iterator closes while waiting for a message.
